\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','HyperDeck Shuttle'),(1525,'<p>Media Express 3.0 will have new features and UI enhancements</p>','',1,'ME',128,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Media Express'),(1528,'','',1,'AT',760,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','ATEM'),(3350,'<p>The Deck!</p>','',0,'HS',36,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Hyperdeck Studio'),(5864,'<p>Shuttle and Studio</p>','',1,'HPD',321,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','HyperDeck'),(6486,'','',1,'VR',0,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Video Recorder'),(10889,'','',1,'BCC',648,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Cameras'),(11074,'','',1,'TR',339,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Teranex'),(14511,'<p>Development Plan<br />\r\n<br />\r\nProduct Name: <br />\r\nCode Name: Dynamic Duo<br />\r\nDoc Version: 1<br />\r\nDoc Date: 20 August 2012<br />\r\nDelivery Date: NAB 2013<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOverview:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEveryone needs to monitor their audio to ensure the correct levels are being recorded. Dynamic Duo is an audio monitoring device with a variety of digital and analog audio inputs. There are two large 33 segment LED meters and small LCD display for the SDI input. Two high quality internal full range speakers and two sub woofers make this the ideal addition to any studio. The basic design will include 6G support with minor component changes when the 6G components become available.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nContents<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1. Connections<br />\r\n2. Form Factor and Panel Layout<br />\r\n3. Buttons and Operation<br />\r\n4. Formats<br />\r\n5. Display<br />\r\n6. Software<br />\r\n7. Compliance<br />\r\n8. Other Requirements<br />\r\n9. Marketing Actions<br />\r\n10. Warranty<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1. Connections:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nComputer Connection<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1 x USB type B for software updates and user configuration. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nPower Connectors<br />\r\n<br />\r\n110/240V 50/60 Hz internal power supply which sources 48V DC. Customers to provide their own IEC cord.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nVideo Connectors<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHDMI Output which supports 8 channels of audio. This is converted from the SDI input. If there is no SDI input the HDMI will output black using the selected audio input.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBNC for SDI with embedded audio Input. Will support all 16 channels.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBNC for SDI and embedded audio Loop out.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAudio Connectors<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOne Female XLR for Balanced 110&Omega; AES/EBU - two channels of audio <br />\r\n<br />\r\nTwo Female XLR for Balanced Analog low impedance line level - left and right channels<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTwo Female RCA for unbalanced analog audio input. Two inputs, for left and right audio. These will be line level inputs. The Right input connector will be red and the Left input connector white.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe order of the connectors from left to right is as follows:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHDMI&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled HDMI OUT<br />\r\nBNC&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled SDI IN<br />\r\nBNC&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled SDI Loop OUT<br />\r\nFemale XLR&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled AES/EBU IN<br />\r\nFemale XLR&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Analog IN R<br />\r\nFemale XLR&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Analog IN L<br />\r\nRCA&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Analog IN L &amp; R<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2. Form Factor and Panel layout<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDynamic Duo will be 1RU and be less than 8&quot; deep. The front panel will have the following:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTwo full range speakers for left and right audio.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTwo subwoofer speakers<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSix small buttons. These buttons be arranged in a 2 x 3 grid.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1/4&quot; headphone socket for professional stereo headphones to be mounted on the left hand side of the enclosure. When headphones are connected the built-in speakers will be muted. Headphone level will be adjusted by the volume control. When plugged in the volume will automatically be set to 50% and the user can adjust to personal taste.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSpeaker volume control with push button will be mounted on the right hand side of the enclosure<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTwo 27 WRGB segment LED meters which are user selectable to be VU or PPM. The left audio channel will be on top and the right audio channel will be underneath. Between both channels the following markings will be printed for VU:<br />\r\nVU&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -20, -10, -7, -5, -3, -2, -1, 0, +1, +2, +3<br />\r\n<br />\r\nA printed stick-on PPM scale will also be available:<br />\r\nPPM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -12, -8, -4, 0, +4, +8, +12<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThese scales are designed around the zero point at +4dBu with a decibel scale ranging <br />\r\nnon-linearly from 20dB below this point to 3dB above for VU and 12dB below this point to 12dB above for PPM.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe color scheme of the LEDs will be configurable from the Configuration tool. By default the color scheme will be:<br />\r\nGreen&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -20 to -6<br />\r\nOrange&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -6 to 0<br />\r\nRed&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0 to +3<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLCD display for viewing SDI input. The top few lines will display SDI format, Stereo or Solo channel, Audio Input source and channel numbers. When there is no SDI input the display will show an Icon based on the current input type. The LCD screen will always display the SDI video input even through audio may be selected from another source.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n3. Buttons and Operation<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere will be six buttons plus the headphone socket to the left of the LEDs. The buttons will be arranged in a 2 x 3 grid. The arrangement will be:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTop left hand button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solo Left&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Left<br />\r\nTop right hand button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solo Right&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Right<br />\r\nMiddle left hand button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Channel No. Up&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Channel Up<br />\r\nMiddle right hand button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Channel No. Down&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Channel Down<br />\r\nBottom left hand button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Input Selector&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Input <br />\r\nBottom right hand button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mute Button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; labeled Mute&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen the Solo Left button is selected both meters and speakers will become mono and will only support the left channel. Pressing Solo Left again will return Dynamic Duo to Stereo mode. When the Solo Right button is selected both meters and speakers will become mono and will only support the right channel. Pressing Solo Right again will return Dynamic Duo to Stereo mode. The LCD display will provide selected information.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe input selector button will cycle from SDI to AES to Analog back to SDI each time the button is pressed. Analog audio will automatically detected between balanced and unbalanced inputs. If both are connected, Balanced will get priority.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen the SDI input is selected, Dynamic Duo will be able to monitor 8 pairs of audio. By default, Dynamic Duo will monitor channels 1 &amp; 2 and by pressing Channel up will change to Channels 3 &amp; 4, Channel 5 &amp; 6 up to Channels 15 &amp; 16. Selecting Channel down will step back to Channels 1 &amp; 2.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe default configuration of the unit will be as follows:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VU meters<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SDI selected<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Channels 1 &amp; 2<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen power cycled, the last know configuration will be recalled.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n4. Formats&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe SDI input should be capable of auto detecting the following formats:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n625/25 PAL<br />\r\n525/29.97 NTSC<br />\r\n720p50<br />\r\n720p59.94<br />\r\n720p60<br />\r\n1080i50<br />\r\n1080i59.94<br />\r\n1080i60<br />\r\n1080PsF23.98<br />\r\n1080PsF24<br />\r\n1080PsF25<br />\r\n1080PsF29.97<br />\r\n1080PsF30<br />\r\n1080p23.98<br />\r\n1080p24<br />\r\n1080p25<br />\r\n1080p29.97<br />\r\n1080p30<br />\r\n1080p50<br />\r\n1080p59.94<br />\r\n1080p60<br />\r\n<br />\r\n5. Display<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe display should have a resolution of 320x240 be clear with text at the top to display the SDI input format, Solo or Stereo, Channel numbers and audio input. <br />\r\nWhen there is no SDI input the display will show an Icon based on the current input <br />\r\ntype instead of the picture. The text on top of the display will still be displayed.<br />\r\nThe LCD screen will always display the SDI video input even through audio <br />\r\nmay be selected from another source.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n6. Software<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDynamic Duo can be configured for PPM or VU operation and color scheme of the LEDs via USB. The USB connection is also used for software updates and should support:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMac OS X<br />\r\n&bull; Lion 10.7.4 <br />\r\n&bull; Mountain Lion 10.8 <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWindows <br />\r\n&bull; Windows 7 32<br />\r\n&bull; Windows 7 64<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the future we may wish to include an equalizer configuration tool but this will not be available in the first release. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>','',1,'AM',39,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','AudioMonitor'),(16431,'<p>Project for testing a range of Blackmagic products with a series of Avid systems on multiple predefined systems.</p>','',1,'APT',600,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Avid ProTools'),(21413,'','',1,'MD',89,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Multidock'),(30858,'<p>Project used by DV group for Pre Testing</p>','',1,'DVP',946,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Desktop Video PreQA'),(35522,'<p>Test Plan used and maintained by Desktop Video Test Group</p>','',1,'MEPQ',125,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Media Express PreQA'),(36294,'<p>Test Plan used and maintained by the Desktop Video Test Group</p>','',1,'DSTPQ',8,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Disk Speed Test PreQA'),(38088,'','',1,'SAND',2,1,'O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:19:\"requirementsEnabled\";i:0;s:19:\"testPriorityEnabled\";i:0;s:17:\"automationEnabled\";i:0;s:16:\"inventoryEnabled\";i:0;}','Sandbox');
